1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,840
 - So good.

2
00:00:00,840 --> 00:00:03,040
 I'm, my name's Andrew.

3
00:00:03,040 --> 00:00:04,760
 I'm one of the pastors here at the Vine.

4
00:00:04,760 --> 00:00:06,960
 And if you're relatively new to the church,

5
00:00:06,960 --> 00:00:09,680
 we're packed in here today with Overflow as well.

6
00:00:09,680 --> 00:00:11,640
 Hey to everybody who's in the Overflow.

7
00:00:11,640 --> 00:00:13,480
 We're so glad you're a part of our community.

8
00:00:13,480 --> 00:00:15,640
 Everybody joining us online.

9
00:00:15,640 --> 00:00:19,840
 My uncle and aunt actually are joining online here today.

10
00:00:19,840 --> 00:00:23,560
 So it's great to have Pam and Ken with us as well.

11
00:00:23,560 --> 00:00:27,960
 As I step into the pulpit here this morning,

12
00:00:27,960 --> 00:00:32,960
 I do so really sensing the importance and the weight

13
00:00:32,960 --> 00:00:35,960
 of the time of history that I think we're in right now.

14
00:00:35,960 --> 00:00:40,360
 And in particular, the importance of our faith,

15
00:00:40,360 --> 00:00:44,760
 our belief in Jesus to actually really mean something

16
00:00:44,760 --> 00:00:45,960
 in the world right now.

17
00:00:45,960 --> 00:00:48,160
 'Cause I don't know about you,

18
00:00:48,160 --> 00:00:51,840
 but I think the world is in a really ugly place right now.

19
00:00:51,840 --> 00:00:53,600
 Anyone else sensing this?

20
00:00:53,600 --> 00:00:55,640
 I think we can see if we're looking at the news

21
00:00:55,640 --> 00:00:58,200
 and our social media feeds,

22
00:00:58,200 --> 00:01:00,760
 it's really easy for us to see that the world

23
00:01:00,760 --> 00:01:03,600
 is more volatile than it's ever been before.

24
00:01:03,600 --> 00:01:05,480
 I would say the world is more violent

25
00:01:05,480 --> 00:01:07,520
 than it's been for a long time.

26
00:01:07,520 --> 00:01:08,800
 The world is more divided.

27
00:01:08,800 --> 00:01:10,480
 There is more hatred.

28
00:01:10,480 --> 00:01:12,240
 There are more challenges.

29
00:01:12,240 --> 00:01:13,640
 I don't know about you, but it's like for me,

30
00:01:13,640 --> 00:01:14,880
 when I'm waking up in the morning,

31
00:01:14,880 --> 00:01:18,760
 I have to take a big deep breath before I open my phone,

32
00:01:18,760 --> 00:01:20,600
 before I jump on my social media feed

33
00:01:20,600 --> 00:01:21,920
 and take a look at the news.

34
00:01:21,920 --> 00:01:24,760
 'Cause I'm wondering what is it gonna be today?

35
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:26,440
 Anyone else feel that way at the moment?

36
00:01:26,440 --> 00:01:28,360
 Like what's the next shooting gonna be?

37
00:01:28,360 --> 00:01:30,800
 What's the next terrorist act going to be?

38
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:33,040
 What's the next stupid thing

39
00:01:33,040 --> 00:01:35,480
 that some leader of some government's gonna say?

40
00:01:35,480 --> 00:01:38,200
 And when we kind of sit in this,

41
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:40,400
 we realise that it's not just one city

42
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:42,440
 or one country or one culture.

43
00:01:42,440 --> 00:01:44,480
 This is kind of a global thing

44
00:01:44,480 --> 00:01:46,280
 that is happening at the moment.

45
00:01:46,280 --> 00:01:50,600
 And this should deeply challenge us as Christians.

46
00:01:50,600 --> 00:01:53,640
 In fact, when we're living in a time

47
00:01:53,640 --> 00:01:55,560
 like we're experiencing right now,

48
00:01:55,560 --> 00:01:58,160
 where it really does feel like the world

49
00:01:58,160 --> 00:02:02,520
 is in a super difficult, challenging, dark and ugly place,

50
00:02:02,520 --> 00:02:07,520
 I think it asks of Christians a very specific question.

51
00:02:07,520 --> 00:02:11,160
 A question to which the answer

52
00:02:11,160 --> 00:02:14,720
 will not only shape the future of the church itself,

53
00:02:14,720 --> 00:02:19,240
 but actually shape the future of the world itself.

54
00:02:19,240 --> 00:02:20,600
 And here's that question.

55
00:02:22,080 --> 00:02:25,200
 What should we do as Christians

56
00:02:25,200 --> 00:02:28,480
 when the world has gone crazy?

57
00:02:28,480 --> 00:02:33,680
 I wonder if you've been asking yourself that question lately.

58
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:37,360
 Like what should we do as believers of Jesus?

59
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:38,640
 As people where the scriptures say

60
00:02:38,640 --> 00:02:41,080
 that the same spirit that raised Jesus from the dead

61
00:02:41,080 --> 00:02:42,200
 is inside of me.

62
00:02:42,200 --> 00:02:44,200
 What should we do as Christians

63
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:47,240
 when the world around us seems to be as crazy

64
00:02:47,240 --> 00:02:49,720
 as it is right now?

65
00:02:49,720 --> 00:02:51,200
 And while I would put it to you

66
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:54,160
 that I think this is the most critical question

67
00:02:54,160 --> 00:02:56,840
 that the global church should be asking right now,

68
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:57,680
 here's the thing.

69
00:02:57,680 --> 00:02:59,440
 It is not the first time

70
00:02:59,440 --> 00:03:01,480
 the church has had to ask that question.

71
00:03:01,480 --> 00:03:05,320
 In fact, if you look back over human history

72
00:03:05,320 --> 00:03:08,040
 and particular over church history,

73
00:03:08,040 --> 00:03:09,680
 there have been many, many times

74
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:11,520
 where it feels like for Christians

75
00:03:11,520 --> 00:03:14,080
 that the world has spun out of control.

76
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:15,400
 Many times where it feels like the world

77
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:17,360
 is suddenly broken out from underneath us

78
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:18,720
 and we're kind of floating

79
00:03:18,720 --> 00:03:21,280
 and we're not sure if we got any solid ground

80
00:03:21,280 --> 00:03:23,840
 for us to land on.

81
00:03:23,840 --> 00:03:25,400
 The question about what Christians should do

82
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:26,800
 when the world has gone crazy

83
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:31,720
 is something Christians have been asking for 2000 years.

84
00:03:31,720 --> 00:03:34,680
 And I wanna show you as we start today

85
00:03:34,680 --> 00:03:39,320
 how I would say there are four primary models

86
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:42,800
 that church over church history has embraced

87
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:46,440
 as an answer to this question of what we should do

88
00:03:46,440 --> 00:03:48,320
 when the world goes crazy.

89
00:03:48,320 --> 00:03:52,880
 Here's the first one, I would say it is to escape.

90
00:03:52,880 --> 00:03:55,240
 And in this idea through church history,

91
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:57,360
 the reality has been is that the world

92
00:03:57,360 --> 00:03:58,360
 looks something like this.

93
00:03:58,360 --> 00:04:01,520
 The world is this depraved, broken, dark,

94
00:04:01,520 --> 00:04:03,720
 kind of ruined place.

95
00:04:03,720 --> 00:04:07,880
 And we as Christians, we find ourselves in a world

96
00:04:07,880 --> 00:04:09,880
 that's spinning out of control,

97
00:04:09,880 --> 00:04:11,440
 in a world that's getting uglier and uglier,

98
00:04:11,440 --> 00:04:13,400
 more divided, more hostile, more violent.

99
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:14,640
 And here's our thought.

100
00:04:14,640 --> 00:04:18,920
 Our thought is, can we just get out of it, please?

101
00:04:18,920 --> 00:04:22,280
 Like if we could just bungee jump out of this world

102
00:04:22,280 --> 00:04:26,800
 and get up to heaven, then finally everything will be okay.

103
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:30,680
 And through church history, there have been theologies

104
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:32,880
 that have helped the church to think about

105
00:04:32,880 --> 00:04:35,200
 what it will be when we get out

106
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:36,880
 of the ugliness of this world,

107
00:04:36,880 --> 00:04:39,920
 that everything burns here so that we can go

108
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:44,080
 and enjoy eternal life on some fluffy cloud up there.

109
00:04:45,080 --> 00:04:47,920
 This kind of thinking kind of came into the church

110
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:51,440
 as early as the third century through the monastic movement.

111
00:04:51,440 --> 00:04:54,280
 Now, the monastic movement had some fantastic things

112
00:04:54,280 --> 00:04:56,760
 about it and to it even to this day.

113
00:04:56,760 --> 00:04:58,880
 But the monastic movement at its heart was this idea

114
00:04:58,880 --> 00:05:02,160
 of let's just get out of the impurity of this world

115
00:05:02,160 --> 00:05:04,840
 so that we can create something where we can find

116
00:05:04,840 --> 00:05:09,360
 just a solid place of purity amongst ourselves.

117
00:05:09,360 --> 00:05:11,880
 What we've seen in church history of the answer

118
00:05:11,880 --> 00:05:13,120
 to the question of what do we do

119
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:14,560
 when the world goes crazy?

120
00:05:14,560 --> 00:05:17,080
 Let's just get out of here.

121
00:05:17,080 --> 00:05:21,280
 The next one that we've seen in church history

122
00:05:21,280 --> 00:05:23,680
 is this one that I like to call insulate.

123
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:27,600
 So on this one, it's not so much the escape,

124
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:29,520
 but it has the same kind of idea.

125
00:05:29,520 --> 00:05:32,840
 Here's the world and the world is that dark and evil

126
00:05:32,840 --> 00:05:34,200
 and broken place.

127
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:38,720
 And here are us Christians and we are in this world.

128
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:40,600
 Whether we like it or not,

129
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:42,520
 the reality is we're in the world.

130
00:05:42,520 --> 00:05:44,000
 Didn't Jesus himself say,

131
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:47,040
 "I've called you to be in the world," right?

132
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:48,280
 But then how does he follow that?

133
00:05:48,280 --> 00:05:49,720
 What does he say?

134
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:50,560
 But not of the world.

135
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:52,120
 He said, "I want you to be in the world,

136
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:53,720
 "but not of the world."

137
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:56,360
 And so there's been a movement through church history

138
00:05:56,360 --> 00:05:59,400
 where it's like, okay, we can't escape this thing.

139
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:01,880
 I guess we're here until we die.

140
00:06:01,880 --> 00:06:03,640
 But whilst we're here, what we're gonna do

141
00:06:03,640 --> 00:06:05,960
 is we're gonna insulate ourselves

142
00:06:05,960 --> 00:06:07,840
 from the darkness and the brokenness

143
00:06:07,840 --> 00:06:10,560
 and the hurt and the pain and everything else in the world.

144
00:06:10,560 --> 00:06:14,680
 If we can just keep the world out of our churches,

145
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:16,200
 everything will be fine.

146
00:06:16,200 --> 00:06:20,240
 And this kind of thought of insulation was really big

147
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:22,120
 in like even just recent church history,

148
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:24,240
 I would say in like the '80s and '90s

149
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:26,720
 where we saw the rise of Christian culture,

150
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:28,440
 particularly in the West.

151
00:06:28,440 --> 00:06:31,360
 And it was like, let's just Christianize everything.

152
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:32,560
 We're gonna Christianize music,

153
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:33,840
 we're gonna Christianize movies,

154
00:06:33,840 --> 00:06:35,400
 we're gonna Christianize TV shows,

155
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:36,680
 we're gonna Christianize education.

156
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:38,480
 Everything's gonna be Christianized.

157
00:06:38,480 --> 00:06:40,600
 And if I'm a Christian and I have a family,

158
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:42,560
 I'm just gonna make sure my family exists

159
00:06:42,560 --> 00:06:47,560
 in a Christian bubble and this horrible world cannot enter.

160
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:49,960
 Are you with me?

161
00:06:49,960 --> 00:06:51,560
 Insulate.

162
00:06:51,560 --> 00:06:53,800
 Now, what we've also seen through church history

163
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:57,240
 is this next one that I call control.

164
00:06:57,240 --> 00:06:58,960
 What do we do when the world seems

165
00:06:58,960 --> 00:07:01,000
 to be spinning out of control?

166
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:02,640
 Well, here's the response to this.

167
00:07:02,640 --> 00:07:05,400
 Again, the world is seen as this dark, terrible, horrible,

168
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:10,000
 it's overwhelmed by sin and brokenness and evil.

169
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:11,720
 But in this response, the response is,

170
00:07:11,720 --> 00:07:14,520
 no, we're not gonna escape, we're not gonna insulate.

171
00:07:14,520 --> 00:07:16,480
 Instead, we're gonna fight back.

172
00:07:16,480 --> 00:07:18,640
 And we're gonna fight back by actually trying

173
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:21,120
 to completely turn all of this thing

174
00:07:21,120 --> 00:07:24,360
 into as much Christianity as possible.

175
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:27,040
 And we're gonna take our Christian religion

176
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:30,840
 and we're gonna try and control everything else.

177
00:07:30,840 --> 00:07:32,320
 Now, in this approach,

178
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:35,120
 the idea sounds good on the surface, doesn't it?

179
00:07:35,120 --> 00:07:36,960
 These two feels a little bit like

180
00:07:36,960 --> 00:07:38,640
 we're trying to escape everything.

181
00:07:38,640 --> 00:07:41,000
 This one though, on the surface, sounds good.

182
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:45,240
 We're just gonna try and turn the world into Christianity.

183
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:48,520
 Now, even though it sounds good,

184
00:07:48,520 --> 00:07:50,680
 here's the problem throughout church history.

185
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:53,480
 The problem is, even though maybe the idea

186
00:07:53,480 --> 00:07:54,960
 of wanting to see all of our cities,

187
00:07:54,960 --> 00:07:57,640
 all of our countries worship Jesus,

188
00:07:57,640 --> 00:08:00,760
 we've come to think that the only way that's going to happen

189
00:08:00,760 --> 00:08:04,000
 is if we take control of the situation.

190
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,680
 And by taking control of the situation,

191
00:08:05,680 --> 00:08:07,960
 church history has shown us that we've done that

192
00:08:07,960 --> 00:08:12,320
 by actually taking worldly mechanisms and worldly power

193
00:08:12,320 --> 00:08:14,640
 and thinking by using worldly power

194
00:08:14,640 --> 00:08:18,840
 to try to Christianize a nation or Christianize a culture,

195
00:08:18,840 --> 00:08:20,480
 that's the right way to go.

196
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:23,640
 And unfortunately, what happens is we take worldly power

197
00:08:23,640 --> 00:08:25,960
 and we dress it up in Christian clothes.

198
00:08:25,960 --> 00:08:28,280
 And we think that we just need

199
00:08:28,280 --> 00:08:30,520
 to legislate the kingdom of God.

200
00:08:30,520 --> 00:08:32,720
 It's more of a top-down approach

201
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:35,200
 where when you look at the role of Jesus

202
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:38,200
 and the life of Jesus and what he tried to speak about

203
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:41,320
 with the disciples, it was a bottom-up influence,

204
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:45,000
 but this one says, "No, we can do it top-down."

205
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:50,000
 This happened in the late 11th century

206
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:52,000
 at the beginning of the Crusades

207
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:53,680
 and it's happened in many different ways.

208
00:08:53,680 --> 00:08:56,640
 And I would argue is currently manifesting itself

209
00:08:56,640 --> 00:08:59,120
 a little bit in some countries in our world

210
00:08:59,120 --> 00:09:01,600
 with the rise of Christian nationalism.

211
00:09:02,600 --> 00:09:06,600
 The fourth one is this idea of conform.

212
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:09,800
 So when the world spins out of control and gets crazy,

213
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:10,920
 what are we going to do?

214
00:09:10,920 --> 00:09:12,120
 Well, here's what we're gonna do.

215
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:15,120
 Yes, the world is broken, it's bad, it's hurting,

216
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:16,280
 there's a lot of suffering

217
00:09:16,280 --> 00:09:18,240
 and we are Christians in that world,

218
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:21,080
 but you know what?

219
00:09:21,080 --> 00:09:24,040
 Let's just not rock the boat a little bit here.

220
00:09:24,040 --> 00:09:25,960
 Let's just, we think that Christianity

221
00:09:25,960 --> 00:09:27,120
 has something to say to the world,

222
00:09:27,120 --> 00:09:29,880
 but let's just be nice.

223
00:09:29,880 --> 00:09:32,160
 Let's just make sure that we're not rocking the boat,

224
00:09:32,160 --> 00:09:34,080
 we're not doing anything crazy,

225
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:36,240
 we're not doing anything that might get us into trouble.

226
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:40,200
 In fact, why don't we just make sure that everybody likes us?

227
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:41,760
 And if everybody likes us,

228
00:09:41,760 --> 00:09:44,240
 then everything's gonna be okay, surely.

229
00:09:44,240 --> 00:09:45,360
 Like that's what we want.

230
00:09:45,360 --> 00:09:48,240
 And so what we do is we end up turning our churches

231
00:09:48,240 --> 00:09:52,200
 into places that feel exactly like the world.

232
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:55,040
 And rather than standing on some of the beliefs

233
00:09:55,040 --> 00:09:56,560
 that we have and some of the scriptures that we have

234
00:09:56,560 --> 00:09:59,280
 and some of the ways in which we are supposed to be different

235
00:09:59,280 --> 00:10:03,280
 living a different renewed story in the world around us,

236
00:10:03,280 --> 00:10:05,080
 we actually begin to look more like the world

237
00:10:05,080 --> 00:10:06,360
 than the world does.

238
00:10:06,360 --> 00:10:10,840
 And we have found ourselves in a place of compromise,

239
00:10:10,840 --> 00:10:13,920
 in a place of kind of consolidating ourselves into the world

240
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:17,480
 and the reality is the world begins to shape the church

241
00:10:17,480 --> 00:10:19,560
 more than the church is shaping the world.

242
00:10:19,560 --> 00:10:21,680
 And when that takes place,

243
00:10:21,680 --> 00:10:23,160
 now this happened in Jesus' time,

244
00:10:23,160 --> 00:10:26,320
 the Sadducees, the Jewish Sadducees were this mindset,

245
00:10:26,320 --> 00:10:27,880
 let's just try to get on with the Romans,

246
00:10:27,880 --> 00:10:30,360
 let's try and kind of work with the Romans

247
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:32,840
 and maybe God will come and do something amazing.

248
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:35,920
 And from that time on, I think this happens an awful lot.

249
00:10:35,920 --> 00:10:38,360
 So I want you to see two things

250
00:10:38,360 --> 00:10:41,400
 in how the church has responded through history

251
00:10:41,400 --> 00:10:44,400
 with this idea of what do we do when the world blows up.

252
00:10:44,400 --> 00:10:45,560
 Now, I want you to notice two things.

253
00:10:45,560 --> 00:10:48,240
 Number one, here's my confession.

254
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:51,400
 I can see myself in all four of these.

255
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:54,120
 Anyone else can do that?

256
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:56,880
 Like if I think about how I have a tendency

257
00:10:56,880 --> 00:11:01,240
 to wanna respond when I see the world kind of go crazy,

258
00:11:01,240 --> 00:11:02,960
 I can find an honest confession

259
00:11:02,960 --> 00:11:04,520
 that there are times when I wanna escape,

260
00:11:04,520 --> 00:11:06,600
 oh Lord, would you take me tonight

261
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:08,920
 'cause I can't take it at the vine anymore.

262
00:11:08,920 --> 00:11:15,200
 Oh, the people, Lord Jesus, rapture me now.

263
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:16,680
 Did you hear apparently that a pastor said

