00:21:29,040 --> 00:21:31,560
 Come on.

527
00:21:32,280 --> 00:21:34,320
 We know they're wrong.

528
00:21:34,320 --> 00:21:36,440
 We know we shouldn't be doing that.

529
00:21:36,440 --> 00:21:37,960
 We wanna keep that private

530
00:21:37,960 --> 00:21:40,760
 because if our boss found it out, we'd get fired.

531
00:21:40,760 --> 00:21:42,960
 If our wife or our spouse found it out,

532
00:21:42,960 --> 00:21:44,200
 we'd probably get divorced.

533
00:21:44,200 --> 00:21:46,320
 And so the stuff that we know is wrong,

534
00:21:46,320 --> 00:21:48,120
 we deem to keep private.

535
00:21:48,120 --> 00:21:50,000
 The stuff we want people to think about us,

536
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:51,200
 we want to bring public.

537
00:21:51,200 --> 00:21:53,040
 But when it comes to the church

538
00:21:53,040 --> 00:21:55,560
 and when the world becomes a dumpster fire,

539
00:21:55,560 --> 00:21:59,120
 we retreat rather than engage.

540
00:22:00,120 --> 00:22:02,720
 And when we do this, I'm not just talking about

541
00:22:02,720 --> 00:22:06,720
 the reality of sharing the gospel and evangelizing Jesus.

542
00:22:06,720 --> 00:22:08,200
 I'm also talking about the fact

543
00:22:08,200 --> 00:22:10,640
 that we often keep as Christians private

544
00:22:10,640 --> 00:22:14,000
 very much our values, very much our behaviors,

545
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:15,880
 very much the things that Christ is doing

546
00:22:15,880 --> 00:22:18,480
 in a process of sanctification in our lives,

547
00:22:18,480 --> 00:22:20,560
 making us more and more like Christ Jesus.

548
00:22:20,560 --> 00:22:22,880
 That stuff we also suppress.

549
00:22:22,880 --> 00:22:25,720
 The very stuff that changes our thinking,

550
00:22:25,720 --> 00:22:28,280
 changes our decisions, changes our thoughts,

551
00:22:28,280 --> 00:22:30,320
 changes our decisions, changes our habits

552
00:22:30,320 --> 00:22:32,200
 that should be shaping and molding us

553
00:22:32,200 --> 00:22:35,160
 to show the world the hands and feet of Jesus.

554
00:22:35,160 --> 00:22:37,440
 This stuff we also keep quiet.

555
00:22:37,440 --> 00:22:40,040
 It's not just, I wanna tell you about Jesus Christ.

556
00:22:40,040 --> 00:22:43,960
 It's also more compassion, more love, more humility,

557
00:22:43,960 --> 00:22:45,240
 more servant heartedness,

558
00:22:45,240 --> 00:22:48,720
 even that we somehow keep private.

559
00:22:48,720 --> 00:22:52,200
 When the Holy Spirit has taught us and changed us

560
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:55,520
 and has called us to live for Him in such a way

561
00:22:55,520 --> 00:22:57,400
 that we need to understand that when the calling

562
00:22:57,400 --> 00:22:58,960
 of a more public faith,

563
00:22:58,960 --> 00:23:01,360
 it's not just for individual benefit.

564
00:23:01,360 --> 00:23:05,680
 When we're called to a more public faith,

565
00:23:05,680 --> 00:23:08,960
 it's so that we might show the love of Christ to the world,

566
00:23:08,960 --> 00:23:12,120
 not just with our words, but also with our actions,

567
00:23:12,120 --> 00:23:15,640
 with our decisions, with our habits, with our character,

568
00:23:15,640 --> 00:23:18,840
 and with the things that we also say.

569
00:23:18,840 --> 00:23:21,680
 And in doing that, people begin to see something

570
00:23:21,680 --> 00:23:23,680
 that in the darkness of the world,

571
00:23:23,680 --> 00:23:26,920
 before that they were not able to see.

572
00:23:27,920 --> 00:23:30,400
 This is why when we think about our response

573
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:31,640
 through church history,

574
00:23:31,640 --> 00:23:36,320
 we can understand that the way is not to escape.

575
00:23:36,320 --> 00:23:39,960
 The way has to be to lean in and to engage,

576
00:23:39,960 --> 00:23:42,920
 but that has to be not through a worldly empire

577
00:23:42,920 --> 00:23:45,040
 and a worldly power model.

578
00:23:45,040 --> 00:23:47,680
 There has to be a better way.

579
00:23:47,680 --> 00:23:53,200
 There has to be another way to engage this world

580
00:23:53,200 --> 00:23:55,440
 that truly brings it to life.

581
00:23:55,480 --> 00:23:58,640
 Dietrich Bonhoeffer writing at the time

582
00:23:58,640 --> 00:24:02,000
 where the world really was a dumpster fire.

583
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:05,240
 In the time of the rise of Nazi Germany

584
00:24:05,240 --> 00:24:07,440
 as a German Christian himself,

585
00:24:07,440 --> 00:24:10,040
 looking at the church around him

586
00:24:10,040 --> 00:24:13,560
 and seeing how conforming the church was

587
00:24:13,560 --> 00:24:18,560
 to a significant moment in history, Bonhoeffer wrote this.

588
00:24:18,560 --> 00:24:20,280
 He said, "Any community of Jesus

589
00:24:20,280 --> 00:24:23,000
 "which wants to be invisible or dominant

590
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:26,560
 "is no longer a community that follows him."

591
00:24:26,560 --> 00:24:33,840
 The prophet Bonhoeffer speaking into our time today,

592
00:24:33,840 --> 00:24:35,320
 I believe.

593
00:24:35,320 --> 00:24:37,880
 As we see all the challenges that are around us,

594
00:24:37,880 --> 00:24:40,840
 this is the deep question we need to be asking ourselves.

595
00:24:40,840 --> 00:24:43,800
 Is there a better way than this?

596
00:24:43,800 --> 00:24:46,800
 And if there is, what does it look like?

597
00:24:46,800 --> 00:24:50,520
 And that's what the next seven weeks are about.

598
00:24:50,520 --> 00:24:51,360
 I'm done.

599
00:24:51,360 --> 00:24:52,200
 Would you stand with me?

600
00:24:52,200 --> 00:24:53,040
 I'm gonna pray.

601
00:24:53,040 --> 00:24:53,880
 No, just don't stand.

602
00:24:53,880 --> 00:24:56,160
 But that's what the next seven weeks are about.

603
00:24:56,160 --> 00:24:57,280
 We wanna open up for you.

604
00:24:57,280 --> 00:24:58,960
 What is the better way?

605
00:24:58,960 --> 00:25:02,400
 There is in my mind, another model.

606
00:25:02,400 --> 00:25:03,840
 There is the model that we see

607
00:25:03,840 --> 00:25:06,200
 in the life, death and resurrection of Jesus.

608
00:25:06,200 --> 00:25:09,440
 The manifesto of Christ that he brings into the world

609
00:25:09,440 --> 00:25:11,840
 and says, this is the way we should be.

610
00:25:11,840 --> 00:25:14,600
 Even if there's an empire, even if there's oppression,

611
00:25:14,600 --> 00:25:17,520
 even if there's persecution, even if there's injustice,

612
00:25:17,520 --> 00:25:19,320
 even if there's the darkness and the hatred

613
00:25:19,320 --> 00:25:21,000
 and the bigotry and everything like that.

614
00:25:21,000 --> 00:25:24,800
 Even when that's alive, this is how we should be

615
00:25:24,800 --> 00:25:27,640
 as the church, as believers in Jesus.

616
00:25:27,640 --> 00:25:31,960
 What we see in the life of Christ is a new and fresh way.

617
00:25:31,960 --> 00:25:34,160
 And so what I wanna do this morning

618
00:25:34,160 --> 00:25:36,160
 is I wanna just start the process

619
00:25:36,160 --> 00:25:38,360
 of shining a light onto this new way.

620
00:25:38,360 --> 00:25:40,960
 And over these next seven weeks, we're gonna unpack that

621
00:25:40,960 --> 00:25:42,960
 as we look at different spheres of influence

622
00:25:42,960 --> 00:25:45,000
 that each one of us has in our lives

623
00:25:45,000 --> 00:25:47,960
 and how we can be living more publicly

624
00:25:47,960 --> 00:25:50,440
 for Christ in those spaces.

625
00:25:50,440 --> 00:25:52,640
 There's a passage at the beginning

626
00:25:52,640 --> 00:25:54,280
 of the Sermon of the Mount,

627
00:25:54,280 --> 00:25:58,240
 Jesus' manifesto of how Christians should be in this world

628
00:25:58,240 --> 00:25:59,440
 from Matthew 5 to 7.

629
00:25:59,440 --> 00:26:01,800
 But there's a bit just at the start of it

630
00:26:01,800 --> 00:26:05,400
 where he speaks directly to how we should be

631
00:26:05,400 --> 00:26:07,440
 when the world has gone crazy.

632
00:26:07,440 --> 00:26:09,200
 And when he's writing this or saying it

633
00:26:09,200 --> 00:26:12,880
 in the original time, it was a crazy world with that empire.

634
00:26:12,880 --> 00:26:14,920
 But even the readers, the first readers

635
00:26:14,920 --> 00:26:19,160
 of the Gospel of Matthew, who probably in about 70 to 75 AD

636
00:26:19,160 --> 00:26:23,040
 had just seen what Nero had done as the emperor

637
00:26:23,040 --> 00:26:25,840
 in destroying the temple, killing many Christians,

638
00:26:25,840 --> 00:26:28,160
 and then reading this and thinking, hang on a sec,

639
00:26:28,160 --> 00:26:31,680
 we want to escape this Greek or Roman empire right now.

640
00:26:31,680 --> 00:26:34,080
 We want to insulate ourselves.

641
00:26:34,080 --> 00:26:37,280
 But even into that moment, here's what Jesus says.

642
00:26:37,280 --> 00:26:39,640
 He's like, you wanna know how to be?

643
00:26:39,640 --> 00:26:40,480
 Here it is.

644
00:26:40,480 --> 00:26:45,840
 You are salt of the earth.

645
00:26:45,840 --> 00:26:47,560
 But if the salt loses its saltiness,

646
00:26:47,560 --> 00:26:49,320
 how can it be made salty again?

647
00:26:49,320 --> 00:26:50,640
 It is no longer good for anything

648
00:26:50,640 --> 00:26:53,560
 except to be thrown out and trampled by people.

649
00:26:53,560 --> 00:26:55,440
 For you are the light of the world.

650
00:26:55,440 --> 00:26:57,960
 A city on a hill cannot be hidden.

651
00:26:57,960 --> 00:27:00,840
 Neither do people light a lamp and put it under a bowl.

652
00:27:00,840 --> 00:27:02,480
 Instead, they put it on its stand

653
00:27:02,480 --> 00:27:05,280
 and it gives light to everyone in the house.

654
00:27:05,280 --> 00:27:10,040
 So in the same way, let your light shine before all people

655
00:27:10,040 --> 00:27:12,960
 that they may see your good deeds

656
00:27:12,960 --> 00:27:16,080
 and praise your Father in heaven.

657
00:27:16,080 --> 00:27:19,520
 Jesus's response to what Christians should do

658
00:27:19,520 --> 00:27:22,080
 when the world goes crazy,

659
00:27:22,080 --> 00:27:25,440
 simply says you are salt and you are light.

660
00:27:25,440 --> 00:27:26,680
 And in these two metaphors,

661
00:27:26,680 --> 00:27:31,160
 he unpacks for us a new and better way.

662
00:27:31,160 --> 00:27:32,440
 Let me just break them down real quick.

663
00:27:32,440 --> 00:27:34,560
 Salt, in Jesus's time,

664
00:27:34,560 --> 00:27:37,160
 salt really carried three specific things.

665
00:27:37,160 --> 00:27:38,920
 Preachers of this passage have come up

666
00:27:38,920 --> 00:27:41,280
 with multiple expressions of what salt can do

667
00:27:41,280 --> 00:27:42,120
 and all that.

668
00:27:42,120 --> 00:27:43,080
 But actually, when you think about

669
00:27:43,080 --> 00:27:45,320
 only through Jesus's eyes, when he said these words,

670
00:27:45,320 --> 00:27:46,440
 you're salt of the earth,

671
00:27:46,440 --> 00:27:48,280
 what were the things that were on Jesus's mind?

672
00:27:48,280 --> 00:27:49,960
 There would only have been three things

673
00:27:49,960 --> 00:27:51,840
 'cause this is the way salt was in those days.

674
00:27:51,840 --> 00:27:55,960
 The first was that salt had incredible value.

675
00:27:55,960 --> 00:28:00,520
 Salt was a rare and invaluable commodity in those days.

676
00:28:00,520 --> 00:28:02,480
 Such a valuable commodity, in fact,

677
00:28:02,480 --> 00:28:05,680
 that a lot of Roman soldiers were paid not with money,

678
00:28:05,680 --> 00:28:07,280
 but paid with salt.

679
00:28:07,280 --> 00:28:09,640
 This is where in the West we get the expression,

680
00:28:09,640 --> 00:28:11,680
 that person's not worth their salt.

681
00:28:11,680 --> 00:28:13,000
 Ever heard that expression?

682
00:28:13,000 --> 00:28:16,160
 It comes from this idea that salt was so valuable

683
00:28:16,160 --> 00:28:18,400
 that soldiers were paid with salt.

684
00:28:18,400 --> 00:28:20,680
 The actual name for it was salarium,

685
00:28:20,680 --> 00:28:24,160
 which is actually where you get the name salary from.

686
00:28:24,160 --> 00:28:26,440
 So this idea, when Jesus says,

687
00:28:26,440 --> 00:28:28,320
 you are salt of the earth,

688
00:28:28,320 --> 00:28:31,040
 he's like saying, you are the value

689
00:28:31,040 --> 00:28:33,200
 that I place in the world.

690
00:28:33,200 --> 00:28:36,280
 So you have this inherent, beautiful value

691
00:28:36,280 --> 00:28:38,480
 'cause you got the gospel inside of you.

692
00:28:38,480 --> 00:28:40,440
 That same spirit that raised Jesus from the dead

693
00:28:40,440 --> 00:28:41,600
 sits inside of you.

694
00:28:41,600 --> 00:28:44,120
 There's so much value and treasure in you

695
00:28:44,120 --> 00:28:45,560
 and I've placed you in the world.

696
00:28:45,560 --> 00:28:48,240
 So when you remain private

697
00:28:48,240 --> 00:28:50,960
 with the value that is inside of you,

698
00:28:50,960 --> 00:28:53,960
 not only are you devaluing yourself,

699
00:28:53,960 --> 00:28:56,000
 you're also devaluing the world.

700
00:28:56,000 --> 00:28:57,840
 Think of it this way.

701
00:28:57,840 --> 00:29:00,640
 It's like getting paid a salary,

702
00:29:00,640 --> 00:29:03,800
 receiving that salary, putting it in a bank account,

703
00:29:03,800 --> 00:29:06,760
 never spending or using that salary,

704
00:29:06,760 --> 00:29:09,000
 and then complaining that you're poor.

705
00:29:10,880 --> 00:29:13,560
 This is what Christians do in the world.

706
00:29:13,560 --> 00:29:17,200
 When we are escaping, insulating or conforming,

707
00:29:17,200 --> 00:29:18,480
 here's what we say.

708
00:29:18,480 --> 00:29:22,520
 We have the Christ, the gospel inside of us,

709
00:29:22,520 --> 00:29:25,120
 but we don't do anything with it

710
00:29:25,120 --> 00:29:27,520
 and we still complain that the world's on fire.

711
00:29:27,520 --> 00:29:30,520
 And Jesus stands by you and says,

712
00:29:30,520 --> 00:29:32,520
 you're the salt of the earth.

713
00:29:32,520 --> 00:29:33,880
 You're the value.

714
00:29:33,880 --> 00:29:35,400
 Yes, the gospel is me, not you,

715
00:29:35,400 --> 00:29:37,440
 but that gospel sits inside of you.

716
00:29:37,440 --> 00:29:39,360
 You're now my hands and feet in the world.

717
00:29:39,360 --> 00:29:40,400
 You bring value.

718
00:29:40,400 --> 00:29:43,200
 And if you don't act, if you don't do,

719
00:29:43,200 --> 00:29:47,200
 if you don't be in the world with the values of the kingdom,

720
00:29:47,200 --> 00:29:49,280
 you're devaluing the world

721
00:29:49,280 --> 00:29:51,240
 and you're not doing what you've been called to do.

722
00:29:51,240 --> 00:29:52,720
 It's simple, he's saying.

723
00:29:52,720 --> 00:29:54,840
 Which is really interesting

724
00:29:54,840 --> 00:29:59,040
 because salt was always designed to be placed on something.

725
00:29:59,040 --> 00:30:00,920
 Salt in a salt shaker is useless.

726
00:30:00,920 --> 00:30:02,360
 Think about it this way.

727
00:30:02,360 --> 00:30:05,760
 In the same way that salt that only exists

728
00:30:05,760 --> 00:30:08,280
 in a salt shaker is useless,

729
00:30:08,280 --> 00:30:11,720
 so is a Christian who only exists in the church.

730
00:30:11,720 --> 00:30:14,640
 Come on church, come on.

731
00:30:14,640 --> 00:30:17,520
 In the same way that salt that only exists

732
00:30:17,520 --> 00:30:21,400
 in a salt shaker and is never poured out is useless,

733
00:30:21,400 --> 00:30:25,360
 so is a Christian who only exists in the church.

734
00:30:25,360 --> 00:30:28,520
 That's not what the church is here for,

735
00:30:28,520 --> 00:30:32,080
 to just gather us together once a week and make us feel good.

736
00:30:32,080 --> 00:30:34,400
 The church, as it says in Ephesians,

737
00:30:34,400 --> 00:30:38,240
 is the manifold wisdom of God to the world.

738
00:30:38,240 --> 00:30:40,600
 We are to be poured out.

739
00:30:40,600 --> 00:30:42,320
 The second thing Jesus would have thought about

740
00:30:42,320 --> 00:30:44,200
 when he says, "You're the salt of the earth,"

741
00:30:44,200 --> 00:30:47,000
 is that salt was a flavor enhancer,

742
00:30:47,000 --> 00:30:48,840
 much in the same way that we use it a lot today

743
00:30:48,840 --> 00:30:50,720
 when we're cooking food in our homes

744
00:30:50,720 --> 00:30:53,280
 and going to restaurants and having food given to us.

745
00:30:53,280 --> 00:30:55,720
 Salt is a flavor enhancer.

746
00:30:55,720 --> 00:30:58,200
 And not only does it bring its own flavor,

747
00:30:58,200 --> 00:31:00,040
 but salt, when it's used right,

748
00:31:00,040 --> 00:31:03,120
 actually brings the flavor out of the meat itself

749
00:31:03,120 --> 00:31:05,120
 or brings the flavor out of the fish

750
00:31:05,120 --> 00:31:07,040
 or whatever it is that it's on.

751
00:31:07,040 --> 00:31:11,680
 It enhances the flavor that is already contained there.

752
00:31:11,680 --> 00:31:14,560
 So when Jesus says, "You are the salts of the earth,"

753
00:31:14,560 --> 00:31:16,680
 what he's saying is, "You are the ones

754
00:31:16,680 --> 00:31:20,440
 "that I'm sending into the world to bring new flavor

755
00:31:20,440 --> 00:31:23,360
 "and to enhance the flavor of that world."

756
00:31:23,360 --> 00:31:26,640
 Almost like without you, the world is dry,

757
00:31:26,640 --> 00:31:30,040
 it is tasteless, it is bland, it is helpless,

758
00:31:30,040 --> 00:31:32,240
 but you, as the salt of the earth,

759
00:31:32,240 --> 00:31:35,200
 are the flavor enhancers in the world.

760
00:31:35,200 --> 00:31:37,880
 And when you are active as a Christian

761
00:31:37,880 --> 00:31:40,400
 in the public spheres that I've placed you in,

762
00:31:40,400 --> 00:31:43,200
 you make things taste better.

763
00:31:43,200 --> 00:31:44,920
 You make the world better,

764
00:31:44,920 --> 00:31:48,640
 which is a different way of thinking than these models.

765
00:31:48,640 --> 00:31:51,120
 'Cause in these models, it's like, "The world is terrible.

766
00:31:51,120 --> 00:31:53,920
 "I just need to get out of it."

767
00:31:53,920 --> 00:31:56,280
 And when Jesus says, "You are the flavor enhancer

768
00:31:56,280 --> 00:31:58,200
 "of the world," what he's saying to you is,

769
00:31:58,200 --> 00:32:00,400
 "You better stay in the world

770
00:32:00,400 --> 00:32:03,040
 "because I've created value in the world.

771
00:32:03,040 --> 00:32:07,080
 "I've created beauty and wonder and goodness in the world.

772
00:32:07,080 --> 00:32:11,160
 "But if the Christians are not present, no one will see it.

773
00:32:11,160 --> 00:32:15,480
 "You are salts of the earth."

774
00:32:15,480 --> 00:32:18,440
 Now, if it's true that salt enhances flavor,

775
00:32:18,440 --> 00:32:21,560
 then could it be that one of the reasons

776
00:32:21,560 --> 00:32:25,880
 why we're seeing so much brokenness in the world today

777
00:32:25,880 --> 00:32:30,000
 is not because evil abounds, but because Christians don't?

778
00:32:31,000 --> 00:32:34,040
 When the church falls silent,

779
00:32:34,040 --> 00:32:38,200
 all people are left with is the tastelessness of the world.

780
00:32:38,200 --> 00:32:39,920
 Come on, church.

781
00:32:39,920 --> 00:32:42,560
 When the church stays silent,

782
00:32:42,560 --> 00:32:45,840
 all there is left is the tastelessness of this world.

783
00:32:45,840 --> 00:32:48,040
 You are salts.

784
00:32:48,040 --> 00:32:49,320
 The third thing he would have thought about

785
00:32:49,320 --> 00:32:52,520
 is that salt was a preservative agent.

786
00:32:52,520 --> 00:32:55,400
 It was the very thing that in an age before refrigeration

787
00:32:55,400 --> 00:32:57,560
 and ice, at least in the Middle East,

788
00:32:57,560 --> 00:33:02,080
 they had no way of preserving the food from decay,

789
00:33:02,080 --> 00:33:04,360
 natural decay and natural going off.

790
00:33:04,360 --> 00:33:06,840
 So salt was used to pack around meat

791
00:33:06,840 --> 00:33:10,240
 or pack around lamb or pack around fish

792
00:33:10,240 --> 00:33:12,840
 to preserve it for the long time

793
00:33:12,840 --> 00:33:14,560
 in an age before refrigeration.

794
00:33:14,560 --> 00:33:16,280
 So when Jesus says to the disciples,

795
00:33:16,280 --> 00:33:18,040
 "You are the salt of the earth,"

796
00:33:18,040 --> 00:33:20,720
 what he's saying is, "You're the preservative agents

797
00:33:20,720 --> 00:33:21,840
 "that I am releasing.

798
00:33:21,840 --> 00:33:26,040
 "I'm literally packing around the culture, around the world

799
00:33:26,040 --> 00:33:29,160
 "so that the world does not decay.

800
00:33:29,160 --> 00:33:31,280
 "Like I don't wanna see the world decay.

801
00:33:31,280 --> 00:33:34,040
 "I don't wanna see the world dark and blank.

802
00:33:34,040 --> 00:33:36,440
 "I don't wanna see evil abound.

803
00:33:36,440 --> 00:33:38,560
 "I wanna see the church rise up.

804
00:33:38,560 --> 00:33:39,680
 "And when you rise up,

805
00:33:39,680 --> 00:33:41,840
 "it's like you're the preservative agent,

806
00:33:41,840 --> 00:33:45,800
 "which ensures that the culture and the world does not decay.

807
00:33:45,800 --> 00:33:49,320
 "'Cause look, I'm not gonna bungee jump you out of here

808
00:33:49,320 --> 00:33:51,480
 "so you can go sit on a fluffy cloud.

809
00:33:51,480 --> 00:33:55,440
 "No, the prayer I taught you is heaven come to earth."

810
00:33:55,440 --> 00:33:58,040
 And the picture in Revelations 21 and 22

811
00:33:58,040 --> 00:34:00,840
 is a new Jerusalem coming to earth.

812
00:34:00,840 --> 00:34:02,040
 And Jesus says these things,

813
00:34:02,040 --> 00:34:07,040
 "Behold, I make all things new, not all new things.

814
00:34:07,040 --> 00:34:14,120
 "So you're the preservative agents of a world

815
00:34:14,120 --> 00:34:16,960
 "that is desperately in decline

816
00:34:16,960 --> 00:34:20,160
 "when you keep your mouth and life shut."

817
00:34:20,160 --> 00:34:22,720
 Think about this.

818
00:34:23,680 --> 00:34:26,440
 When Christians remain private in their faith,

819
00:34:26,440 --> 00:34:29,440
 they contribute to the decaying of the world.

820
00:34:29,440 --> 00:34:33,720
 It's pretty strong.

821
00:34:33,720 --> 00:34:35,920
 So Jesus lays this all out.

822
00:34:35,920 --> 00:34:38,480
 And then he says, "You're light of the world."

823
00:34:38,480 --> 00:34:39,440
 Which is fascinating

824
00:34:39,440 --> 00:34:41,040
 because when he says, "You're light of the world,"

825
00:34:41,040 --> 00:34:43,720
 later on, he's gonna say, "I'm the light of the world."

826
00:34:43,720 --> 00:34:45,880
 But here he says, "You're the light of the world."

827
00:34:45,880 --> 00:34:46,720
 What he's saying is,

828
00:34:46,720 --> 00:34:49,520
 here's what happens when you go into the public spheres

829
00:34:49,520 --> 00:34:52,280
 with your faith, again, sharing the gospel,

830
00:34:52,280 --> 00:34:54,200
 but also living the values of the kingdom

831
00:34:54,200 --> 00:34:55,400
 publicly before you.

832
00:34:55,400 --> 00:34:57,080
 When you do that, he's saying,

833
00:34:57,080 --> 00:34:59,960
 "It's like you're shining a bright bolt of lightning

834
00:34:59,960 --> 00:35:02,240
 "into the darkness that is around."

835
00:35:02,240 --> 00:35:03,960
 And here's what that light does.

836
00:35:03,960 --> 00:35:07,840
 Yes, number one, it shines a light on what is broken

837
00:35:07,840 --> 00:35:10,720
 and decaying and what is evil and sin

838
00:35:10,720 --> 00:35:14,200
 and helps people to see that they can repent

839
00:35:14,200 --> 00:35:15,880
 and find new life in Christ.

840
00:35:15,880 --> 00:35:17,240
 Absolutely.

841
00:35:17,240 --> 00:35:20,600
 When we share the gospel and live the gospel publicly,

842
00:35:20,600 --> 00:35:22,440
 we are inviting people in to realize

843
00:35:22,440 --> 00:35:24,520
 that the way that they're living right now is not right,

844
00:35:24,520 --> 00:35:26,680
 but that there is a loving and faithful God

845
00:35:26,680 --> 00:35:28,480
 who will forgive them in repentance

846
00:35:28,480 --> 00:35:30,280
 and birth them into new life.

847
00:35:30,280 --> 00:35:34,760
 But it also means that when the light shines

848
00:35:34,760 --> 00:35:37,640
 through a church that moves publicly in his faith,

849
00:35:37,640 --> 00:35:40,120
 the things that are good in the world

850
00:35:40,120 --> 00:35:42,520
 that people prior to that could not see

851
00:35:42,520 --> 00:35:45,080
 are illuminated again for them.

852
00:35:45,080 --> 00:35:47,480
 That the hopelessness that people feel,

853
00:35:47,480 --> 00:35:50,120
 the way of looking and saying, "Nobody here is good.

854
00:35:50,120 --> 00:35:51,080
 "Nobody loves me.

855
00:35:51,080 --> 00:35:52,920
 "Everybody hates me."

856
00:35:52,920 --> 00:35:56,120
 When we as Christians begin to show love, live love,

857
00:35:56,120 --> 00:35:57,880
 be love to the ones around us

858
00:35:57,880 --> 00:36:00,160
 who are so darkened by the brokenness around them,

859
00:36:00,160 --> 00:36:02,880
 they can begin to see that there is hope,

860
00:36:02,880 --> 00:36:05,280
 hope in Jesus Christ first and foremost,

861
00:36:05,280 --> 00:36:08,960
 and hope in the world and the body that he's created.

862
00:36:08,960 --> 00:36:13,520
 It's beautiful invitation to be this light.

863
00:36:13,520 --> 00:36:17,960
 So when the world goes crazy and we're tempted to think

864
00:36:17,960 --> 00:36:20,200
 that it's either to privatize ourself,

865
00:36:20,200 --> 00:36:22,680
 to escape or insulate or conform,

866
00:36:22,680 --> 00:36:25,400
 we have to realize that, no, we've been called to engage,

867
00:36:25,400 --> 00:36:28,560
 but not engage in a way that takes worldly power

868
00:36:28,560 --> 00:36:30,680
 and dresses it up in the name of Jesus

869
00:36:30,680 --> 00:36:33,960
 and tries to control from the top down,

870
00:36:33,960 --> 00:36:37,120
 but a world in which we as the salt and light

871
00:36:37,120 --> 00:36:38,840
 move from the bottom up,

872
00:36:38,840 --> 00:36:43,680
 offering hope and preservation and flavor enhancement

873
00:36:43,680 --> 00:36:46,120
 and shining light so that people can see

874
00:36:46,120 --> 00:36:48,600
 and the world begins to shift and change.

875
00:36:48,600 --> 00:36:50,160
 One of my favorite New Testament scholars

876
00:36:50,160 --> 00:36:52,520
 is a guy by the name of Craig Blomberg.

877
00:36:52,520 --> 00:36:54,080
 He's brilliant on the parables

878
00:36:54,080 --> 00:36:56,680
 and he's written on this idea of salt and light.

879
00:36:56,680 --> 00:36:58,760
 Let me read you what he writes.

880
00:36:58,760 --> 00:37:00,880
 He says, "Both the metaphors of salt and light

881
00:37:00,880 --> 00:37:02,760
 "raise important challenges

882
00:37:02,760 --> 00:37:05,520
 "about Christian involvement in society.

883
00:37:05,520 --> 00:37:08,760
 "We are not called to control secular power structures,

884
00:37:08,760 --> 00:37:11,240
 "neither are we promised that we can Christianize

885
00:37:11,240 --> 00:37:13,560
 "the legislation and values of the world.

886
00:37:13,560 --> 00:37:17,960
 "Instead, we must remain active, preservative agents,

887
00:37:17,960 --> 00:37:20,520
 "indeed, irritants," love that word,

888
00:37:20,520 --> 00:37:23,200
 "in calling and revealing to the world

889
00:37:23,200 --> 00:37:25,160
 "God's heart of love."

890
00:37:25,160 --> 00:37:28,520
 We are active, preservative agents

891
00:37:28,520 --> 00:37:31,600
 of a world that God has created and that He loves so much.

892
00:37:31,600 --> 00:37:35,600
 We are irritants to the evil and the sin

893
00:37:35,600 --> 00:37:37,040
 and the brokenness of this world,

894
00:37:37,040 --> 00:37:40,400
 to the injustice which grasps a hold of so many people.

895
00:37:40,400 --> 00:37:43,520
 We get to live a better model.

896
00:37:43,520 --> 00:37:45,320
 And Jesus points to what that is

897
00:37:45,320 --> 00:37:48,000
 right at the end of verse 16 here.

898
00:37:48,000 --> 00:37:49,800
 He says this, "In the same way,

899
00:37:49,800 --> 00:37:53,120
 "let your light shine before people that they may see,"

900
00:37:53,120 --> 00:37:55,960
 what? "Your good deeds."

901
00:37:55,960 --> 00:37:58,680
 So what's Jesus' model?

902
00:37:58,680 --> 00:38:01,080
 It's not escape, it's not insulate, it's not control,

903
00:38:01,080 --> 00:38:02,640
 it's not conform.

904
00:38:02,640 --> 00:38:04,600
 What Jesus is saying, there's another way,

905
00:38:04,600 --> 00:38:06,360
 and here's the summary of that way,

906
00:38:06,400 --> 00:38:09,880
 "Your good deeds."

907
00:38:09,880 --> 00:38:11,840
 In the Greek, if you translate these words,

908
00:38:11,840 --> 00:38:15,560
 it means this, beautiful or lovely works.

909
00:38:15,560 --> 00:38:18,600
 Not talking about moral good,

910
00:38:18,600 --> 00:38:23,600
 talking about wonder and creativity and beauty and love.

911
00:38:23,600 --> 00:38:26,360
 He's like, "The deeds you do

912
00:38:26,360 --> 00:38:29,160
 "that brings my beauty to the world."

913
00:38:29,160 --> 00:38:32,960
 Now, what are those deeds?

914
00:38:32,960 --> 00:38:36,160
 Well, it's interesting 'cause Jesus starts this section,

915
00:38:36,160 --> 00:38:37,880
 we're looking at with a direct thing.

916
00:38:37,880 --> 00:38:39,360
 He says, "You are the salt."

917
00:38:39,360 --> 00:38:40,680
 He says, "You are the light."

918
00:38:40,680 --> 00:38:41,640
 And right at the end, he says,

919
00:38:41,640 --> 00:38:43,640
 "Because you're doing these deeds.

920
00:38:43,640 --> 00:38:46,360
 "And when you do these deeds, people will glorify Jesus."

921
00:38:46,360 --> 00:38:47,200
 And so we're left to say,

922
00:38:47,200 --> 00:38:50,520
 "Well, what are those deeds, Jesus?"

923
00:38:50,520 --> 00:38:52,200
 Well, he's already answered that

924
00:38:52,200 --> 00:38:53,920
 before he even gets to this passage.

925
00:38:53,920 --> 00:38:55,880
 So let's jump back and have a look at what he says

926
00:38:55,880 --> 00:38:57,760
 right at the beginning of the chapter

927
00:38:57,760 --> 00:38:59,800
 in verse three of chapter five.

928
00:38:59,800 --> 00:39:02,200
 "Blessed are the poor in spirit,

929
00:39:02,200 --> 00:39:03,960
 "for theirs is the kingdom of heaven.

930
00:39:03,960 --> 00:39:06,320
 "Blessed are those who mourn, for they will be comforted.

931
00:39:06,320 --> 00:39:08,960
 "Blessed are the meek, for they will inherit the earth.

932
00:39:08,960 --> 00:39:11,520
 "Blessed are those who hunger and thirst for righteousness,

933
00:39:11,520 --> 00:39:12,720
 "for they will be filled.

934
00:39:12,720 --> 00:39:15,480
 "Blessed are the merciful, for they will be shown mercy.

935
00:39:15,480 --> 00:39:18,200
 "Blessed are the pure in heart, for they will see God.

936
00:39:18,200 --> 00:39:20,360
 "Blessed are the peacemakers,

937
00:39:20,360 --> 00:39:23,040
 "for they will be called sons and daughters of God.

938
00:39:23,040 --> 00:39:24,840
 "Blessed are those who are persecuted

939
00:39:24,840 --> 00:39:26,160
 "because of righteousness,

940
00:39:26,160 --> 00:39:28,400
 "for theirs is the kingdom of heaven.

941
00:39:28,400 --> 00:39:32,160
 "Blessed are you when people insult you, persecute you,

942
00:39:32,160 --> 00:39:35,280
 "falsely say all kinds of evil against you because of me.

943
00:39:35,280 --> 00:39:39,880
 "Rejoice and be glad, because great is your reward in heaven

944
00:39:39,880 --> 00:39:42,520
 "for in the same way they persecuted the prophets

945
00:39:42,520 --> 00:39:43,880
 "who were before you."

946
00:39:43,880 --> 00:39:46,880
 You are the salt of the earth.

947
00:39:46,880 --> 00:39:50,560
 You are, in other words, what he's saying is

948
00:39:50,560 --> 00:39:55,000
 being salt and light is not a command, it's a response.

949
00:39:55,000 --> 00:39:59,480
 It's a response out of what we are doing

950
00:39:59,480 --> 00:40:01,400
 as we live our faith more publicly.

951
00:40:01,400 --> 00:40:03,720
 And what does it mean to live our faith publicly?

952
00:40:03,720 --> 00:40:05,240
 It means to mourn with those who mourn.

953
00:40:05,240 --> 00:40:06,800
 It means to stand with the peacemakers.

954
00:40:06,800 --> 00:40:07,960
 It means to be merciful.

955
00:40:07,960 --> 00:40:08,920
 It means all of the things

956
00:40:08,920 --> 00:40:10,240
 that we just read in the Beatitudes,

957
00:40:10,240 --> 00:40:13,120
 that does not sound like escaping, insulating, conforming,

958
00:40:13,120 --> 00:40:15,640
 and it definitely doesn't sound like controlling.

959
00:40:15,640 --> 00:40:18,200
 It sounds like a better way.

960
00:40:18,200 --> 00:40:20,800
 Now, when we read the Beatitudes,

961
00:40:20,800 --> 00:40:23,120
 we often read it like this, that I need,

962
00:40:23,120 --> 00:40:25,520
 if God blesses these kinds of people,

963
00:40:25,520 --> 00:40:27,840
 the poor in spirit, the meek,

964
00:40:27,840 --> 00:40:29,560
 the ones that are peacemakers,

965
00:40:29,560 --> 00:40:33,120
 then I need to be those people and God will bless me.

966
00:40:33,120 --> 00:40:34,520
 So oftentimes when we read the Beatitudes,

967
00:40:34,520 --> 00:40:36,840
 we put ourselves in the position

968
00:40:36,840 --> 00:40:38,920
 of the person who's getting blessed.

969
00:40:38,920 --> 00:40:40,000
 Do you follow that?

970
00:40:40,000 --> 00:40:41,120
 So I just need to be more meek.

971
00:40:41,120 --> 00:40:43,000
 I just need to be, this is the kind of person I need to be

972
00:40:43,000 --> 00:40:44,440
 to get God's blessing.

973
00:40:44,440 --> 00:40:46,400
 When Jesus says, "You are the salt of the world.

974
00:40:46,400 --> 00:40:47,520
 "You are the light of the world

975
00:40:47,520 --> 00:40:49,560
 "because you're doing these beautiful, lovely deeds,"

976
00:40:49,560 --> 00:40:51,600
 what Jesus is saying at the beginning of the Beatitudes

977
00:40:51,600 --> 00:40:52,480
 is actually different.

978
00:40:52,480 --> 00:40:55,040
 He's not saying, "Be the one who is the meek

979
00:40:55,040 --> 00:40:56,000
 "and the mild person."

980
00:40:56,000 --> 00:40:58,200
 He's saying, "Here's the role of the church.

981
00:40:58,200 --> 00:40:59,960
 "Here's the role of the Christian.

982
00:40:59,960 --> 00:41:03,840
 "You are the ones to bless the peacemakers.

983
00:41:03,840 --> 00:41:06,280
 "You are the ones to bless the meek.

984
00:41:06,280 --> 00:41:08,880
 "You are the ones to bless those who mourn.

985
00:41:08,880 --> 00:41:11,560
 "You are the ones to bless those who hunger

986
00:41:11,560 --> 00:41:13,120
 "and thirst for righteousness.

987
00:41:13,120 --> 00:41:16,600
 "You're the ones who do these lovely, beautiful things

988
00:41:16,600 --> 00:41:19,480
 "of blessing as I would bless

989
00:41:19,480 --> 00:41:21,800
 "when the church moves in my heart,

990
00:41:21,800 --> 00:41:23,840
 "when the church moves in my spirit

991
00:41:23,840 --> 00:41:26,000
 "and comes around those who are hurting and broken

992
00:41:26,000 --> 00:41:27,280
 "and vulnerable and marginalized

993
00:41:27,280 --> 00:41:31,440
 "and seeks to bless, seeks to love, seeks to offer grace.

994
00:41:31,440 --> 00:41:35,240
 "This is what changes the darkness in the light.

995
00:41:35,240 --> 00:41:38,880
 "This is what takes the world and brings its flavor.

996
00:41:38,880 --> 00:41:41,400
 "You are the ones to bless."

997
00:41:41,400 --> 00:41:45,440
 Those are the lovely deeds, the good deeds,

998
00:41:45,440 --> 00:41:49,040
 the beautiful deeds that when people see you do it,

999
00:41:49,040 --> 00:41:51,600
 their inclination is not, "You're amazing."

1000
00:41:51,600 --> 00:41:56,160
 Their inclination is, "I never knew God was like that."

1001
00:41:57,160 --> 00:42:02,160
 So when we hear rhetoric about hate coming from the church,

1002
00:42:02,160 --> 00:42:06,280
 when we see rhetoric about power and control

1003
00:42:06,280 --> 00:42:09,760
 and top down coming from the church,

1004
00:42:09,760 --> 00:42:15,560
 we have to sit again in these profound words of Jesus

1005
00:42:15,560 --> 00:42:18,760
 and think again about what it means to not be private,

1006
00:42:18,760 --> 00:42:21,360
 but to be public, but not in a way that leads

1007
00:42:21,360 --> 00:42:23,960
 to some Christian nationalism,

1008
00:42:23,960 --> 00:42:26,080
 but in a way that offers the gospel

1009
00:42:26,080 --> 00:42:28,720
 as Jesus always intended it to be offered.

1010
00:42:28,720 --> 00:42:32,600
 To those that desperately need it,

1011
00:42:32,600 --> 00:42:35,600
 shining light in the darkness of sin,

1012
00:42:35,600 --> 00:42:38,360
 shining light into the goodness of the world,

1013
00:42:38,360 --> 00:42:42,880
 preserving, enhancing, creating value.

1014
00:42:42,880 --> 00:42:46,120
 That, my friends, is the church alive.

1015
00:42:46,120 --> 00:42:48,920
 But the church is only alive when we decide

1016
00:42:48,920 --> 00:42:51,600
 to move from a place of privacy in our faith

1017
00:42:51,600 --> 00:42:53,480
 to a place of living for Christ.

1018
00:42:53,480 --> 00:42:54,320
 As he called us to.

1019
00:42:54,320 --> 00:42:55,760
 And over the next seven weeks,

1020
00:42:55,760 --> 00:42:57,360
 that's what we're gonna unpack

1021
00:42:57,360 --> 00:42:59,440
 in all the areas of your lives.

1022
00:42:59,440 --> 00:43:00,920
 Amen?

1023
00:43:00,920 --> 00:43:01,960
 Could you stand with me?

1024
00:43:01,960 --> 00:43:03,480
 I would love to pray with you.

1025
00:43:03,480 --> 00:43:09,080
 Father, I thank you so much

1026
00:43:09,080 --> 00:43:11,720
 for each person here in this room,

1027
00:43:11,720 --> 00:43:15,360
 in our overflow, those that are watching online right now.

1028
00:43:15,360 --> 00:43:19,280
 Father, we pray we come to you in prayer,

1029
00:43:19,280 --> 00:43:21,360
 recognizing at the start of this seven weeks

1030
00:43:21,360 --> 00:43:23,960
 that we are desperate for this new model.

1031
00:43:23,960 --> 00:43:27,720
 Grateful that you look at us and speak over us

1032
00:43:27,720 --> 00:43:30,720
 and say you are salt, you are light.

1033
00:43:30,720 --> 00:43:34,920
 Father, would you help us where we recognize

1034
00:43:34,920 --> 00:43:37,480
 that the escape, insulate, control, and conform

1035
00:43:37,480 --> 00:43:40,040
 is still well and alive in the global church,

1036
00:43:40,040 --> 00:43:42,400
 is still well and alive inside of me,

1037
00:43:42,400 --> 00:43:44,240
 and I'm sure many of us in this room.

1038
00:43:44,240 --> 00:43:49,560
 Lord, would you help us to not just see

1039
00:43:49,560 --> 00:43:50,840
 that there's a better way,

1040
00:43:51,120 --> 00:43:53,120
 but begin to walk in a better way.

1041
00:43:53,120 --> 00:43:57,800
 And Father, where we're tempted to,

1042
00:43:57,800 --> 00:44:03,680
 in a time like this, ironically, keep our faith more quiet.

1043
00:44:03,680 --> 00:44:07,360
 Father, I pray you would light a fire

1044
00:44:07,360 --> 00:44:08,520
 in people in this room,

1045
00:44:08,520 --> 00:44:12,160
 to have the urgency,

1046
00:44:12,160 --> 00:44:17,000
 the urgency not to escape, to insulate,

1047
00:44:17,000 --> 00:44:19,840
 to control or conform.

1048
00:44:20,400 --> 00:44:23,720
 But the urgency to serve like you served,

1049
00:44:23,720 --> 00:44:28,720
 the urgency to wash the feet of the people around us,

1050
00:44:28,720 --> 00:44:31,560
 the urgency to love our enemy,

1051
00:44:31,560 --> 00:44:36,040
 the urgency to offer grace, the urgency to mourn,

1052
00:44:36,040 --> 00:44:38,800
 the urgency to bless the peacemakers,

1053
00:44:38,800 --> 00:44:40,960
 the urgency to reach out to the people

1054
00:44:40,960 --> 00:44:43,560
 that the rest of society seems to be condemning

1055
00:44:43,560 --> 00:44:44,960
 and ignoring and avoiding.

1056
00:44:44,960 --> 00:44:48,760
 Would you give us an urgency to be like you?

1057
00:44:49,360 --> 00:44:51,960
 (gentle music)

1058
00:44:51,960 --> 00:44:55,240
 I just want you to take a moment

1059
00:44:55,240 --> 00:44:57,040
 just in the quietness of your heart.

1060
00:44:57,040 --> 00:44:59,480
 Maybe there's a confession for you

1061
00:44:59,480 --> 00:45:00,920
 to bring to the Lord today.

1062
00:45:00,920 --> 00:45:04,640
 As Jesus is present with you now,

1063
00:45:04,640 --> 00:45:06,200
 no condemnation that comes,

1064
00:45:06,200 --> 00:45:08,280
 he's not whacking you with a stick,

1065
00:45:08,280 --> 00:45:11,200
 but there is this beautiful sense of conviction

1066
00:45:11,200 --> 00:45:12,160
 that does come,

1067
00:45:12,160 --> 00:45:15,120
 when we realize that we've drifted

1068
00:45:15,120 --> 00:45:16,400
 from being salt and light.

1069
00:45:18,120 --> 00:45:21,200
 Where we realize that we've decided to embed ourselves more

1070
00:45:21,200 --> 00:45:26,160
 in the privacy and the personal nature of our faith.

1071
00:45:26,160 --> 00:45:30,040
 And perhaps your prayer today is just to ask the Lord

1072
00:45:30,040 --> 00:45:31,800
 to forgive you for that natural tendency

1073
00:45:31,800 --> 00:45:32,760
 that you might have.

1074
00:45:32,760 --> 00:45:38,040
 Ask him to show you how you can break

1075
00:45:38,040 --> 00:45:40,920
 the temptation to privacy in this time.

1076
00:45:40,920 --> 00:45:45,880
 And then invite him to strengthen your courage.

1077
00:45:47,400 --> 00:45:49,600
 To strengthen your resolve.

1078
00:45:49,600 --> 00:45:56,400
 And to show you once again, the beautiful, lovely deeds.

1079
00:45:56,400 --> 00:45:58,960
 The simple things this week that you can do.

1080
00:45:58,960 --> 00:46:02,640
 To serve as Jesus would serve.

1081
00:46:02,640 --> 00:46:06,000
 To make the world a better place.

1082
00:46:06,000 --> 00:46:08,320
 Father, we thank you that this gospel of yours

1083
00:46:08,320 --> 00:46:09,560
 is counter-cultural.

1084
00:46:09,560 --> 00:46:12,960
 On the surface, it sounds weak.

1085
00:46:15,720 --> 00:46:17,640
 But Lord, this gospel of yours

1086
00:46:17,640 --> 00:46:20,880
 means that there is no other name

1087
00:46:20,880 --> 00:46:22,360
 that is higher than your name.

1088
00:46:22,360 --> 00:46:26,000
 As we sang in that song earlier,

1089
00:46:26,000 --> 00:46:28,040
 that we would take the place of suffering

1090
00:46:28,040 --> 00:46:29,480
 so that we would rise in you.

1091
00:46:29,480 --> 00:46:31,800
 Lord, I pray that in this time

1092
00:46:31,800 --> 00:46:33,360
 where the world has gone crazy,

1093
00:46:33,360 --> 00:46:36,080
 we would not escape, we would not insulate.

1094
00:46:36,080 --> 00:46:41,080
 We would reign in the fear that drives control.

1095
00:46:43,760 --> 00:46:48,760
 And we would stand against the conformity that comes.

1096
00:46:48,760 --> 00:46:52,480
 And we'd be salt and light again.

1097
00:46:52,480 --> 00:46:56,400
 And we thank you for this in Jesus' name.

1098
00:46:56,400 --> 00:46:58,080
 Everyone says, amen.

1099
00:46:58,080 --> 00:46:59,840
 Let's continue to worship together.

1100
00:46:59,880 --> 00:47:02,480
 (gentle music)

1101
00:47:02,480 --> 00:47:05,060
 (gentle music)

